{
  "doc_id": "19562",
  "text": "Lactate has been shown to be elevated in rodent glioma models [CITATION_1] . It is well known that neoplastic cells have an increased capacity for glycolytic metabolism (7) under both aerobic or anaerobic conditions as part of the malignant phenotype, thus the lactate signal would be expected to be elevated [CITATION_2] . Additionally, measuring the concentration of lactate in animal models has been used to monitor response to both chemotherapy and radiotherapy [CITATION_3] .",
